{"legislative_session": "20252026", "identifier": "AB1685", "title": "Driving privilege: points.", "from_organization": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["bill"], "subject": ["Drivingprivilege", "points"], "abstracts": [{"note": "summary", "abstract": "Existing law establishes that specified convictions, violations, and traffic-related incidents count as points against a driver's record for purposes of the suspension or revocation of the privilege to drive. Existing law imposes 2 violation points each against a driver's record for purposes of the suspension or revocation of the privilege to drive if a driver is convicted of vehicular manslaughter, including driving a vehicle in the commission of an unlawful act, not amounting to a felony, and with gross negligence, or driving a vehicle in connection with automobile insurance fraud where the vehicular collision or accident was knowingly caused for financial gain and proximately resulted in the death of any person.\n\nThis bill would increase the violation points to 3 against a driver's record for a conviction of the above-described driving offenses."}], "other_titles": [], "other_identifiers": [{"identifier": "ocd-bill-ca-20252026-ab1685"}], "actions": [{"description": "Read first time. To print.", "date": "2026-02-02", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["reading-1"], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "From printer. May be heard in committee March 5.", "date": "2026-02-03", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": [], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "Referred to Coms. on PUB. S. and TRANS.", "date": "2026-02-17", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["referral-committee"], "related_entities": [{"name": "Coms. on PUB. S. and TRANS.", "entity_type": "organization", "organization_id": null}]}, {"description": "In committee: Set, first hearing. Hearing canceled at the request of 